// bisect: fusion/JIT WRONG-VALUE bug, nondeterministic — soak jul07h
// fuzz/divergence_000001, the first wrong-answer manifestation of the
// fusion-shape flap (task #19). A callee kernel (`helper`) inlines a
// fold whose callback captures helper's param `x`; when the capture's
// instantiation BindId drifted (run-to-run, the type/shape flap),
// JitEnv::lookup's unrestricted NAME fallback resolved `x` to the fold
// ELEMENT binding — which FoldQ name-binds as literally "x" — so slot
// 1 read the element 3 instead of the captured 5: interp 19, jit 17
// on ~5/6 runs (19 on the rest). FIXED: the name fallback serves only
// id-LESS synthetic locals; a same-named local with a DIFFERENT real
// id is a distinct binding, and a missed capture id Errs the site (the
// region de-fuses — never a wrong answer). The never-by-name
// discipline of audit-jul2026/03, applied to the emit env. The id
// DRIFT itself is the still-open #19 investigation.
// mutant: {use array; let helper = |x: i64| -> i64 array::fold([x, i64:3], i64:0, |a, b| a + x + i64:1 * b); let outer = |x: i64| -> i64 helper(x) + i64:1; outer(i64:5)}
// minimized:
{f64:0.; let helper = |x: i64| -> i64 array::fold([x, i64:3], i64:0, |a, b| a + x + i64:1 * b); let outer = |x: i64| -> i64 helper(x) + i64:1; outer(i64:5)}
